<br>
The room is in shambles. Maeroth’s bed is turned on its side, books and parchments are strewn about the room, glass shards from vials of ink lie strewn about the floor, and mysterious liquids drip from glass bottles turned over on their shelves.  You look carefully at the ogre, and recognize something is not quite right about him.  He seems… wrong somehow.  With a small degree of trepidation, you stoop down to take a closer look at this beast, and you soon discover the ogre is not dead at all, but is sleeping.  Looking over the ogre more carefully, you find something extremely puzzling! The beast is wearing many trinkets of arcane magic?!  An iron amulet of unseen horrors?! An iron scroll of war?! Grandmaster Jewelers eyeglasses?!  Things start to fall into place as you spy something else…<br>
<br>
“What is this?!”, you say as you see the Staff of the Serpent clutched in the ogre’s hand.  You know that such an item is imprinted to its owner and cannot be stolen.  No, this hulk who lies here is no ogre.  It must be, it <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">has</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to be..<br>
<br>
“Maeroth!”, you yell as you stoop down to try and wake the beast up but it is to no avail. He does not stir.  You call for help, but no one answers your call.<br>
<br>
Some kind of liquid spatters against your cheek.  As you wipe the slimy substance from your face, you look up to see the source.  Liquid mana drips onto the wooden desk from a shelf overhead, sending spatters of the precious fluid into the air, all over the desk, and into a small old, leather-bound book that has been left carelessly open.  You stand up, and return the vial of mana to its upright position and pick up the tomb to protect it from the acrid liquid.  You take out a silk rag from a pouch at your waist and dab the pages of the book to absorb the liquefied mana.<br>
<br>
As you do so, something catches your eye.  The soft, delicate, flowing script that can be seen on the top half of the left page, starkly contrasts the large, messy printed writings on the other side.  Upon closer inspection, you realize what you hold… Maeroth’s journal. You read the last passage to try to understand what has happened to this poor Enchanter.<br>
<br>
